sudo su
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade
sudo service bluetooth start
cat etc/*release*

To install app from reporsitory:
        sudo apt install libreoffice   ///fullname of app without spaces

To install app from .tar.gz file (archived):
        Download the desired .tar.gz or (.tar.bz2) file
        Open Terminal
        Extract the .tar.gz or (.tar.bz2) file with the following commands
        tar xvzf PACKAGENAME.tar.gz
        tar xvjf PACKAGENAME.tar.bz2
        Navigate to the extracted folder using cd command
        cd PACKAGENAME
        Now run the following command to install the tarball
        ./configure
        make
        sudo make install

To install a .deb file: 
            sudo dpkg -i package_file.deb
To uninstall a .deb file: 
            sudo apt-get remove package_name.


To list all devices: xinput list
To disable keypad: xinput float 16
To enable Keypad: xinput reattach 16 3
///Ref: https://askubuntu.com/questions/160945/is-there-a-way-to-disable-a-laptops-internal-keyboard